						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">NES games could use the BRK instruction if they wanted to, it just triggers an interrupt, and sets a flag somewhere to indicate that the interrupt was generated by a BRK instruction.</div><br />But the only one I'm aware of that actually does that is Galaxian, probably because of a 6502 design quirk related to when NMI and BRK execute at once.</div>

